{"id":"335440954_Ordering_groups_constructively","abstract":"The existence of a linear order on a group that is compatible with the group structure generally requires transfinite methods. However, this can be circumvented by concentrating on the consistency of a suitable propositional theory. To this end, we work with Scott’s multiple-conclusion entailment relations to describe the positive cones of a group. The commutative case then leads to a constructive version of Levi’s theorem that an Abelian group be orderable if and only if it is torsion-free. Subsequently, Cederquist and Coquand’s fundamental theorem of entailment relations prompts a finitary version of Sikora’s theorem.","authors":["Daniel Wessel"],"meta":["August 2019Communications in Algebra 47(3):1-21","DOI:10.1080/00927872.2018.1477947"],"references":["329410461_Cut_elimination_for_entailment_relations","258516222_Lattice_Theory_Foundation","232808855_Convergence_in_Formal_Topology_a_unifying_notion","231901135_Geometric_Hahn-Banach_theorem","228799102_Hidden_constructions_in_abstract_algebra_Krull_Dimension_of_distributive_lattices_and_commutative_rings","331848665_Ordering_groups_and_validity_in_lattice-ordered_groups","321124513_An_introduction_to_Lorenzen's_Algebraic_and_logistic_investigations_on_free_lattices_1951","320818233_Stone_bases_alias_the_constructive_content_of_Stone_representation","320512451_Eliminating_disjunctions_by_disjunction_elimination","318163837_Proof_Theory_and_Ordered_Groups","317773817_ELIMINATING_DISJUNCTIONS_BY_DISJUNCTION_ELIMINATION","313596653_Untersuchungen_fiber_das_logische_Schliessen","313592617_A_discrete_variant_of_Farkas'_Lemma","312521058_Lattice-ordered_groups_generated_by_ordered_groups_and_regular_systems_of_ideals","311842241_Extension_by_Conservation_Sikorski's_Theorem","299045789_Transfer_theorems_and_intuitionistic_set_theory","290096220_Intuitionistic_Formal_Spaces_-_A_First_Communication","286355813_Set_Theory_Boolean-Valued_Models_and_Independence_Pr